  "opposite_reasoning": "Reasoning provides the strongest semantic opposition to Perception for Fisher-LDA steering. It captures the fundamental cognitive distinction between sensory-empirical processing (perception: seeing, hearing, feeling) and abstract-logical processing (reasoning: inferring, deducing, analyzing). This axis is highly relevant for AI safety as it helps distinguish between systems that merely pattern-match sensory data vs those that perform genuine logical inference. The perception-reasoning axis maps to important AI capabilities: perceptual AI (vision models, speech recognition) vs reasoning AI (theorem provers, causal models). Both concepts clearly exist in SUMO and WordNet with rich semantic structure. While Perception lacks a true antonym, Reasoning offers the most useful complementary opposition for understanding cognitive architecture."
